SENATE RESOLUTION NO. 107
BY SENATOR BOUDREAUX
CONDOLENCES. Expresses sincere and heartfelt condolences on the passing of Mr. Joel
Parker Sr.
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To express the sincere condolences of the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana upon the
3 death of Joel Parker Sr.
4 WHEREAS, it is with deep regret and profound sorrow that the citizens of Louisiana
5 learned of the peaceful transition into eternal life of Joel Parker Sr. on April 17, 2026, at the
6 age of eighty-nine; and
7 WHEREAS, Joel Parker Sr., was born on March 23, 1937 to Ezola Young in
8 Washington, Louisiana, where he accepted Christ and was baptized at an early age, and
9 served as a devoted member of Wiley United Methodist Church in Blanks, Louisiana; and
10 WHEREAS, Joel Parker Sr. was united in holy matrimony to Elnora Murray on
11 January 21, 1960, with their union being blessed with four daughters and two sons and they
12 shared thirty-five years of love and devotion until her passing on June 3, 1995; and
13 WHEREAS, he developed a passion for horses at a young age and became known
14 as one of the finest cowboys, horse trainers, and rodeo event presenters with himself having
15 competed in rodeos as a saddle bronc rider and bull rider; and
16 WHEREAS, despite the challenges of not being welcome as a black cowboy, Joel
17 fought against the odds and became a Stock and Rodeo Producer in Louisiana and
18 Mississippi, bringing black and white cowboys together; and
