1 WHEREAS, for over fifty years Joel hosted rodeos where he was recognized as a
2 strong inspiration to the many young people involved in his rodeos at the Lottie Stampede
3 Arena, alongside his sons and rodeo partner, Eli Allen. Their Easter Sunday Rodeo became
4 a cherished family tradition for many years; and
5 WHEREAS, Joel Parker Sr. was a faithful and hardworking man who worked for the
6 Weinstein' Haas-Herschel Ranch; the JE Jumonville Ranch; the OD Kent Ranch; and later
7 retired from the Alma Plantation in early 2000; and
8 WHEREAS, Joel leaves behind many cherished memories for his family and friends
9 who will remember the warmth of his love, the brilliance of his spirit, and his love for
10 horses; and
11 WHEREAS, he is survived by his children: Augustine Parker of Lottie, Cherry
12 Bridgewater of St. Francisville, Joel Parker Jr. of Lottie, James Parker of Krotz Springs,
13 Barbara (Dale) Howard of Glynn, and Norma (Ronald) Zachery of Lottie, all in Louisiana,
14 and eleven grandchildren: Corey (Margaret) Parker, Brett Parker, Precious (Jessie) Tate,
15 Madonna Parker, Dyamond Parker, Brittany Howard, Tre' Beckman, Courtney Parker, Jamie
16 Williams, Dante' Williams, Jordan Philson, and J'Niyah Parker, and twenty-five great
17 grandchildren; and
18 WHEREAS, he is also survived by his sister and brothers-in-law: Adrian Tezeno,
19 Geraldine Andrus, Willie Murray, John Murray, Joel Murray Sr., Grace (Melvin) White, and
20 Beverly (Tilden) Boudreaux, and a host of nieces, nephews, other relatives, and dear friends;
21 and
22 WHEREAS, Joel also shared a special bond with Freddie Nolan who he considered
23 a son; Quincy Battley, a co-worker and dear friend; and Lavale Johnson, who was like a
24 grandson to him; and
25 WHEREAS, Joel leaves behind extremely close cowboy friends who were
26 considered family: Gene Richard, Errol Klein, Luke Decuir, Darrell Cezair, Willie King,
27 Eugene King, Ray Dunbar, Pokey Johnson, Leniel Kimble, Mitch Wyble, JB Stelly, Dude
28 Warts and countless others; and
29 WHEREAS, he was preceded in death by his beloved wife, Elnora Parker; his mother
30 and step-father, Ezola and Arthur Skinner; his father and mother-in-law, Arthur and
