4 and
5 WHEREAS, the success of the state of Louisiana, the strength of its communities,
6 and overall vitality of American society depends in great measure on people like Joel Parker
7 Sr., who upon developing their talents and skills, pass their knowledge to the next generation
8 of family members and friends.
9 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the Senate of the Legislature of Louisiana
10 does hereby express sincere and heartfelt condolences upon the death of Joel Parker Sr. and
11 does extend enduring appreciation for the tremendous pride and honor that he leaves forever
12 to his community, the state of Louisiana, and the United States of America.
13 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
14 family of Joel Parker Sr.
